column6: The correct answer is Independent t-test!
column11: A linguist wants to compare the occurrence of nouns in two of his favorite Shakespeare plays, As You Like It and Julius Caesar. He counts them all, stores them in this dataset and wants to know if the number of nouns in the two plays differ from each other.

column10: Null: There is no difference in the occurrence of nouns in As You Like It and Julius Caesar.
Alternative: There is a difference in the occurrence of nouns in As You Like It and Julius Ceasar.
The occurrence of nouns in As You Like It and Julius Caesar are the same.
